    "department": "Product",
    "description": "WHY HARVEY\n\nAt Harvey, we’re transforming how legal and professional services operate — not incrementally, but end-to-end. By combining frontier agentic AI, an enterprise-grade platform, and deep domain expertise, we’re reshaping how critical knowledge work gets done for decades to come.\n\nThis is a rare chance to help build a generational company at a true inflection point. With 1000+ customers in 60+ countries, strong product-market fit, and world-class investor support, we’re scaling fast and defining a new category in real time. The work is ambitious, the bar is high, and the opportunity for growth — personal, professional, and financial — is unmatched.\n\nOur team is sharp, motivated, and deeply committed to the mission. We move fast, operate with intensity, and take real ownership of the problems we tackle — from early thinking to long-term outcomes. We stay close to our customers — from leadership to engineers — and work together to solve real problems with urgency and care. If you thrive in ambiguity, push for excellence, and want to help shape the future of work alongside others who raise the bar, we invite you to build with us.\n\nAt Harvey, the future of professional services is being written today — and we’re just getting started.\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nAt Harvey, we’re transforming how legal and professional services operate – not incrementally, but end-to end. By combining frontier agentic AI, an enterprise-grade platform, and deep domain expertise, we’re reshaping how critical knowledge work gets done for decades to come. As we scale, our Enterprise Product organization sits at the center of this mission — connecting the systems our customers use, and scaling into new customer segments \u0026 verticals.\n\nWe’re looking for a Product Manager with a strong technical foundation and the ability to own and solve complex product and commercial challenges end-to-end. This person will focus on building out integrations with strategic partners and vendors as well as enable search over data source using MCP’s and deep research. You will help architect systems to bring legal context into Harvey and also work with our Partnerships org and internal teams to prioritize which ones to build. This role is equal parts product intuition and technical execution. You’ll be trusted to make fast, high-quality decisions, ship impactful features, work on the cutting edge of applied AI and grow a team that embodies engineering excellence\n\nWe move with urgency, bias toward simplicity, and expect our leaders to be hands-on when needed. If you’re energized by ownership, decisive execution, and solving real user problems, we'd love to hear from you.\n\nThis role is based in San Francisco, CA. We use an in-person work model (3 days a week) and offer relocation assistance to new employees.\n\n\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Lead the end-to-end product lifecycle, from ideation and strategy to execution and launch\n\n - Collaborate closely with engineering and partnerships team to identify and execute on high-impact integrations\n\n - Work closely with engineers to build, platformize and scale integrations, working cross functionally with adjacent teams\n\n - Expand the breadth and depth of integrations into the Harvey platform\n\n - Collaborate cross-functionally with Product Engineering, Applied AI, Research, and Platform teams to deliver high-quality production systems that support reasoning, summarization, and legal research workflows.\n\n\nWHAT YOU HAVE\n\n - 5+ years of experience building enterprise products in a B2B/commercial environment\n\n - Experience working on Integrations and partnering with cross functional and Partnerships teams\n\n - Experience with or knowledge of AI and LLMs\n\n - Ability to partner with engineers on technical architecture, with enough depth to challenge assumptions, propose solutions, and influence design.\n\n - Ability to navigate extreme ambiguity to deliver outcomes\n\n - A product mindset for balancing user needs, domain complexity, and system constraints to propose high-leverage improvements.\n\n\nCOMPENSATION RANGE\n\n$220,000 - $260,000 USD\n\n\nDEPENDING ON YOUR LOCATION, AN APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICE MAY APPLY TO YOU. YOU CAN FIND ALL OF OUR APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICES [HERE https://www.notion.so/harveyai/Harvey-Candidate-Privacy-Policies-319ac3fcdd7a803bb807d5094f249922].\n\n#LI-ML1\n\nHarvey is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy or related condition, or any other basis protected by law.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made by emailing accommodations@harvey.ai",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
